{"id":33438,"date":"2019-09-12T13:46:36","date_gmt":"2019-09-12T09:46:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=33438"},"modified":"2019-09-12T13:49:17","modified_gmt":"2019-09-12T09:49:17","slug":"umar-convinces-abu-bakr","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/12\/umar-convinces-abu-bakr\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Mushaf: Umar convinces Abu Bakr to collect the Quran"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Zayd ibn Thabit reported: Abu Bak sent for me after the people of Al-Yamamah were killed and Umar ibn al-Khattab was with him. Abu Bakr, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cUmar came to me and said that many reciters of the Quran were killed in the fighting at Al-Yamamah, saying: I am afraid more reciters will be killed in battles to come and much of the Quran will be lost, and I think you should order for the Quran to be compiled. I said to Umar: How can you do something that was not done by the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him? Umar said: By Allah, this will be a good thing. Umar continued to appeal to me until Allah opened my heart to that and I saw the good in it that Umar saw.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4701<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u062b\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u062a\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0628\u064f\u0648 \u0628\u064e\u0643\u0652\u0631\u064d \u0645\u064e\u0642\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629\u0650 \u0641\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0